#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:6
msgid ""
"Lighting is a very important topic in rendering, standing equal to modeling, materials and textures. The most "
"accurately modeled and textured scene will yield poor results without a proper lighting scheme, while a "
"simple model can become very realistic if skillfully lit."
msgstr ""
"灯光在渲染中是一个非常重要的主题, 和建模，材质，纹理一样重要. 最准确的模型和纹理场景没有一个适当的灯光方案都将"
"会产生糟糕的结果,相反一个简单的模型设置合适的灯光将会产生很逼真的效果。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:13
msgid "Viewing Restrictions"
msgstr "查看限制"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:15
msgid "The color of an object and the lighting of your scene is affected by:"
msgstr "物体的颜色和场景的灯光受以下的影响:"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:17
msgid "Your ability to see different colors (partial color blindness is common)."
msgstr "你能够看到不同的颜色(部分色盲的人是很常见的)。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:18
msgid "The medium in which you are viewing the image (e.g. an LCD panel versus printed glossy paper)."
msgstr "你正在查看图像的媒介 (例如LCD显示器面板与打印纸)。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:19
msgid "The quality of the image (e.g. a ``jpeg`` at 0.4 compression versus 1.0)."
msgstr "图像的品质(例如一个JPEG 0.4压缩比到 1.0压缩比)."

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:20
msgid ""
"The environment in which you are viewing the image (e.g. a CRT monitor with glare versus in a dark room, or "
"in a sunshiny blue room)."
msgstr "查看图像的环境(例如一个 CRT 显示器在一个暗的房间或一个阳光充足的房间的显示)."

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:22
msgid ""
"Your brain's perception of the color and intensity relative to those objects around it and the world "
"background color, which can be changed using color manipulation techniques using Blender :doc:`Composite "
"Nodes </compositing/introduction>`."
msgstr ""
"你的大脑的感知颜色和强度相对于周围的物体和世界背景颜色，可以使用Blender 的合成节点（ :doc:`Composite Nodes </"
"compositing/introduction>`）的色彩处理技术来改变。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:29
msgid "Global Influences"
msgstr "全局影响"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:31
msgid "In Blender, the elements under your control which affect lighting are:"
msgstr "在 Blender, 以下的控制要素会影响光照效果:"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:33
msgid "The color of the world :doc:`ambient light </render/cycles/world>`."
msgstr "世界环境光（ :doc:`ambient light </render/cycles/world>`）的颜色。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:34
msgid ""
"The use of :ref:`Ambient Occlusion <render-cycles-integrator-world-ao>` as a way to cast that ambient light "
"onto the object."
msgstr ""
"使用AO（ :ref:`Ambient Occlusion <render-cycles-integrator-world-ao>` ）作为一种计算环境光投射到物体上的一种方"
"法。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:36
msgid ""
"The degree to which the ambient light colors the :doc:`material </render/cycles/materials/index>` of the "
"object."
msgstr "物体上的材质（ :doc:`material </render/cycles/materials/index>` ）环境光颜色的程度。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:38
msgid ""
"The use of :doc:`Indirect lighting </render/eevee/indirect_lighting>`, where the color of one object radiates "
"onto another."
msgstr ""
"采用间接照明( :doc:`Indirect lighting </render/eevee/indirect_lighting>` )，其中一个物体的颜色辐射到另一个物体"
"上。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:40
msgid "The :doc:`lamps </render/lighting/lamp_panel>` in your scene."
msgstr "你场景中的灯光 （ :doc:`lamps </render/lighting/lamp_panel>` ）"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:42
msgid ""
"The physics of light bouncing around in the real world is simulated by Ambient Occlusion (a world setting), "
"buffer shadows (which approximate shadows being cast by objects), ray tracing (which traces the path of "
"photons from a light source). Also, within Blender you can use :doc:`Indirect lighting </render/eevee/"
"indirect_lighting>`. Ray tracing, ambient occlusion, and indirect lighting are computationally intensive "
"processes. Blender can perform much faster rendering with its internal scan line renderer, which is a very "
"good scan line renderer indeed. This kind of rendering engine is much faster since it does not try to "
"simulate the real behavior of light, assuming many simplifying hypotheses."
msgstr ""
"光在现实世界的反弹物理特性是由AO（Ambient Occlusion）模拟的（世界设置）, 缓冲阴影buffer shadows (这是物体投射"
"的近似阴影), 光线追踪（ray tracing ） (追踪来自光源的光子路径). 此外，在Blender可以使用间接照明( :doc:"
"`Indirect lighting </render/eevee/indirect_lighting>` )。光线追踪，AO，间接照明是计算机密集型的过程。Blender使"
"用其内部的扫描线渲染器可以执行得更快，这是确实一个很好的扫描线渲染器。这种渲染引擎的速度要快得多，因为它并不试"
"图模拟光的真实行为，假设许多简化的假设。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:54
msgid "Lighting Settings"
msgstr "灯光设置"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:56
msgid ""
"Only after the above global influences have been considered, do you start adding light from lamps in your "
"scene. The main things under your control are the:"
msgstr "只有在考虑了上述全局影响之后，才开始在场景中添加灯光。下面是你掌控的主要内容："

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:60
msgid "Type of light used (*Sun*, *Spot*, *Lamp*, *Hemi*, etc.)."
msgstr "灯光的类型（*阳光*，*点光*，*半球光*  等）。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:61
msgid "Color of the light."
msgstr "灯光的颜色。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:62
msgid "Position of the light and its direction."
msgstr "灯光的位置和方向。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:63
msgid "Settings for the light, including energy and falloff."
msgstr "灯光的设置，包括亮度（energy） 和衰减（falloff）。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:65
msgid "Then you are back to how that material's shader reacts to the light."
msgstr "然后你将返回到材质着色器 看其是怎么影响灯光。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:67
msgid ""
"This chapter attempts to address the above, including how lights can work together in rigs to light your "
"scene. In this chapter we will analyze the different types of light in Blender and their behavior; we will "
"discuss their strong and weak points."
msgstr ""
"这一章试图解决以上所述问题，包括灯光设备如何协同工作一起照亮场景的。在这章我们将分析Blender中的不同灯光类型和"
"它们和它们的行为；我们将讨论他们的长处和短处。我们也讨论灯光设备。包括最流行的3点打光法。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:74
msgid "Lighting in the Workflow"
msgstr "照明工作流"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:76
msgid ""
"In this user manual we have placed Lighting before Materials; you should set up your lighting before "
"assigning materials to your meshes. Since the material shaders react to light, without proper lighting, the "
"material shaders will not look right, and you will end up fighting the shaders, when it is really the bad "
"lighting that is causing you grief. All of the example images in this section do not use any material setting "
"at all on the ball, cube or background."
msgstr ""
"在本用户手册中，我们将照明置于材质之前; 你应该在指定给你网格材质前设置灯光。因为材质着色器对光有反应，没有适当"
"的灯光 ，材质着色器将看起来是不正确的，坏的照明引起你的不快，你将最终会一直忙在着色器。在这部分的例子球，立方"
"体或者背景将不使用任何的材质。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:86
msgid "Overriding Materials to Reset Lighting"
msgstr "覆盖材质以重置照明"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:90
msgid "Material field in the Render Layers panel."
msgstr "渲染层面板中的材质字段。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:92
msgid ""
"If you have started down the road of assigning materials, and are now fiddling with the lighting, we suggest "
"that you create a default, generic gray material -- no *Vertex Color*, no *Face Texture*, no *Shadeless*, "
"just plain old middle gray with RGB(0.8, 0.8, 0.8). Name this \"Gray\"."
msgstr ""
"如果你已经开始指定材质，正在处理灯光照明，我们建议你创建一个默认的，通用的灰色的物质——没有 *顶点的颜色*，没有 "
"*面纹理* 没有 *阴影*，只是普通的中灰色RGB值为（0.8,0.8，0.8）。命名叫 “Gray”。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/introduction.rst:98
msgid ""
"Next go to the *Render Layer* tab. In the *Layer* panel, select your new \"Gray\" material in the *Material* "
"field. This will override any materials you may have set, and render everything with this color. Using this "
"material, you can now go about adjusting the lighting. Just empty this field to get back to your original "
"materials."
msgstr ""
"接下来到 *Render Layer* 选项卡. 在 *Layer* 面板, 在 *Material* 区域选择你新建的 “Gray” 材质。这将覆盖你以前创"
"建的任何材质，并用这个材质颜色渲染。使用这个材质你现在可以校正灯光。你只需清空这个材质就可以返回到原始材质。"
